	merge: is used to merge two data frames either by common columns or row names 
	joins : are usually used to add columns from y -> x based on the matching rows they have mentioned. 
	dat_map is where the longitude and latitude are saved in the df |
	wdi :  is where the country names with their GDP , emissions and other geographic details are stored. 
	by="ccode" : is the common column in both which does full join , joining both the data frames together with their matching columns 


